# Minimal change first

1. Prefer the smallest, localized change that fully satisfies the request.
2. Preserve existing behavior and update mechanisms unless the user explicitly asks for behavioral changes.
3. For display-only requests, do not alter data flow, timeline logic, refresh behavior, or architecture.
4. Only propose or implement larger refactors when the user explicitly asks for architecture-level improvements.
5. If a broader change could introduce regression risk, call out the risk and default to the minimal safe option.
